The above provided line of code **WebElement email =driver.findElement(By.xpath(&quot;//*[@id=\&quot;email\&quot;]&quot;)).isDisplayed();**  will throw an compilation error &quot;WebElement cannot be resolved to a type&quot; due to type mismatch.The reason behind is:

email type is WebElement and &#39;isDisplayed()&#39; method return type is Boolean. You are assigning Boolean value type to WebElement type which is incorrect.


The correct way to use them in your framework are given below:

1. WebElement email =  driver.findElement(By.xpath(&quot;//*[@id=\&quot;email\&quot;]&quot;));

   Boolean emailDisplayed = email.isDisplayed();

2. Boolean emailDisplayed = driver.findElement(By.xpath(&quot;//*[@id=\&quot;email\&quot;]&quot;)).isDisplayed();

