It&#39;s a bad idea to call scan.next() in an if statement.  The second scan.next will only be called if the first equals is true and so on for the second one, so it is very easy to mix up what columns you&#39;re trying to read.  Move those scan.next out of the if statement for starters.

From the error message, you are calling `Integer.parseInt(i);` on a date string.

It looks like you are trying to find the largest number in the file?  What you should be doing is storing the highest int, which is declared outside the loop.  e.g.

    int Highscore = 0;
    while (...) {
       .... 
    
      int num = Integer.parseInt(i);
      if (num &gt; Highscore) {
        Highscore = num;
      } 

If you get my drift.

If you keep using scan.next in your conditional statements, your scanner will scan for the next value. I think you want to get the next value and use for your comparison instead.

